  "What is spherical aberration?": "",
  "An optical defect where rays far from the principal axis focus at slightly different points than rays close to the axis, causing a blurred image": "",
  "The separation of white light into colors when viewed through a simplified analytical lens": "",
  "The bending of light around obstacles given that prevailing spherical conditions tend to reinforce this particular trajectory": "",
  "The absorption of light by lens material regardless of prevailing conditions in practice": "",
  "Spherical aberration occurs because spherical mirrors and lenses focus rays at different distances from the center at slightly different points. It causes blurring and can be corrected with parabolic mirrors or aspheric lenses.": "",
  "What is chromatic aberration?": "",
