  "The loss of light intensity through a lens, as conventional aberration theory would suggest": "",
  "The darkening at the edges of an image when the interaction between aberration and chromatic factors is taken into full account": "",
  "An optical defect in lenses where different wavelengths of light are focused at slightly different points due to dispersion, causing color fringing": "",
  "Chromatic aberration occurs because the index of refraction varies with wavelength (dispersion). Different colors focus at different distances, creating color fringes around images. It is corrected using achromatic doublets.": "",
  "An object is placed 30 cm from a concave mirror with focal length 10 cm. Where is the image formed?": "",
  "30 cm in front of the mirror": "",
  "10 cm behind the mirror": "",
  "7.5 cm in front of the mirror": "",
  "15 cm in front of the mirror": "",
  "Using 1/f = 1/do + 1/di: 1/10 = 1/30 + 1/di. 1/di = 1/10 - 1/30 = 3/30 - 1/30 = 2/30. di = 15 cm (in front of the mirror, real image).": "",
